    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>All formulas assume SI units. The cross product in the Lorentz force is computed as a scalar magnitude here (q*v*B*sin theta) since our Scheme REPL lacks vector operations. Crowell develops the vector form in detail. The solenoid formula assumes an ideal infinite solenoid; real solenoids have fringe fields at the ends.</p>

